      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a draft rejection email that balances professionalism with kindness:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were impressed by your exceptional technical skills and the enthusiasm you brought to the final interview. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we recognize the value you would bring to our team. Your passion for software development and commitment to excellence are truly admirable, and we appreciate the time you invested in our hiring process. We wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors and hope that our paths will cross again soon.\n\nThank you for your interest in our company, and we wish you continued success in your career.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nI hope this draft meets your requirements. You can modify it to fit your tone and style.",
